==English==

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[sīthe]]''

{{rfap}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# An instrument for [[mow]]ing [[grass]], [[grain]], or the like, by hand, composed of a long, [[curving]] [[blade]], with a sharp edge, made fast to a long handle, called a [[snath]], which is bent into a form convenient for use.
# A scythe-shaped blade attached to ancient war [[chariots]].

